  "nursesNote": "In a fire the nurse follows RACE in order: Rescue anyone in immediate danger first, sound the Alarm (pull the alarm and call the code), Confine the fire by closing doors and windows, and then Extinguish a small fire or Evacuate. Oxygen sources are turned off because oxygen fuels fire, and patients on oxygen are protected. During evacuation, ambulatory patients are moved first, then those needing more help, using stairs rather than elevators. To use a fire extinguisher the nurse uses PASS: Pull the pin, Aim at the base of the fire, Squeeze the handle, and Sweep side to side. Exits are kept clear and staff know the fire plan ahead of time.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Follow RACE: Rescue, Alarm, Confine, Extinguish/Evacuate",
    "Rescue patients in immediate danger first",
    "Turn off oxygen sources and protect oxygen-dependent patients",
    "Evacuate ambulatory patients first using stairs, not elevators",
    "Use PASS to operate a fire extinguisher"
  ],
